The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 May is 42,179 (4,881.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 May, there were 45 new confirmed cases (5.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 May, there were 74 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 39% (29 fewer cases).
